The '''Australian National Shipwreck Database''' is an online, searchable database of over 7,000 known [[shipwreck]]s located around the coast of [[Australia]] and within its inland waters. Originally developed by the [[Australasian Institute of Maritime Archaeology]], it is now maintained by the [[Department of the Environment (Australia)|Department of the Environment]].

