{{Infobox museum | name = Mireuksaji Museum | native_name = Mireuksaju bakmulgwan | established = 1994 | location = [[Iksan]], {{flag|South Korea}} | type = Relics Exhibition | director = Jong Wook Chae | president = Han Ok Baek | website = [http://www.mireuksaji.org/eng Mireksaji Museum] }}
This city was once a capital of [[Baekje]]. This museum displays and preserves the relics excavated from the site where there had been Mireuksaji Buddhist temple before in [[Iksan]], [[South Korea]]. It holds different cultural events and summer school for students. Through this, it puts a lot of effort to be a national museum.<ref>{{cite news|title=익산미륵사지유물전시관 국립박물관 승격 '파란불'|url=http://news1.kr/articles/1330831|newspaper=News1|date=2013-09-23}}</ref> Also it runs various exhibitions and seminars. It opens from 9am to 6pm on weekdays, and it closes on every Monday and the first of January of every year.
