[[File:EAST ELEVATION, WITH SCALE - Courthouse, 600 Second Street, Natchitoches, Natchitoches Parish, LA HABS LA-1310-10.tif|thumb|350px|Old Courthouse Museum in [[Natchitoches, Louisiana|Natchitoches]].]] The '''Old Courthouse Museum – Natchitoches''' is a former courthouse is located at 600 Second Street [[Natchitoches, Louisiana|Natchitoches]], [[Louisiana]].
The museum was formerly operated as a branch of [[Louisiana State Museum]] that displayed temporary exhibits of art and local history. It is no longer open to the public as a museum.<ref>{{cite web|title=Natchitoches Genealogy Library|url=http://www.natchitoches.net/attractions/old-courthouse-state-museum/|publisher=Natchitoches.Net|accessdate=22 April 2015}}</ref>
The second floor of the building houses the Natchitoches Genealogy Library, which includes historic maps, conveyances, mortgages and books, census records and other genealogical papers. The library is open to the public.
==Courthouse architecture== The courthouse building, built in 1896, designed in the [[Richardsonian Romanesque]] style by the architectural firm of [[Favrot and Livaudais]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lsm.crt.state.la.us/natch3.htm|title=Natchitoches, Louisiana|accessdate=2009-07-25}}</ref> A brick [[clock tower]] rises above the building.
The brick courthouse is a [[historic district contributing property]] in the [[Natchitoches Historic District]], of the [[Cane River National Heritage Area]] [[File:Telephoto view of the tower from the southeast - Courthouse, 600 Second Street, Natchitoches, Natchitoches Parish, LA HABS LA-1310-7.tif|thumb|left|225px|Courthouse [[clock tower]].]]
